instruction:
Set the variable `p` and assign it the value of the perimeter of the rectangle (an arbitrary non-negative number).

Set the variable `a` and assign it the value of the first side of the rectangle (an arbitrary non-negative number that is less than `p`).

Set the variable `b`, in which you calculate the second side of the rectangle using the formula `b = p / 2 - a`.

Here is an example that is fundamentally similar to what needs to be done, but adapt it to the requirements of the task:
```javascript
const z = 10;
const x = 1;
const y = z / 2 - x ;
```

